    <item>
      <title>Aloo Tikki</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/blog/aloo-tikki/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 31 Jul 2023 11:19:53 +0530</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/blog/aloo-tikki/</guid>
      <description>&lt;center&gt;&#xA;&lt;img src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/blog/pictures/tikki.png&#34; height=&#34;400px&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/center&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Its the conflicting flavours, red caramelized chutney with its heavy spicy taste and the green, sour tangy  refreshing coriander chutney. The hot tikki just out of the wok, straight into some chilled yoghurt. A contrast of temperature. The depth and texture of the brown deep fried tikki  being contrasted by the homogenous white yoghurt. On top it may be graced by a salad dressing, of chopped onions, cabbage and pomegranate further producing opposition to the deep fried carbohydrates of the tikki.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
